Apart from that, use [**`ExpressionWrapper`**](https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/2.2/ref/models/expressions/#django.db.models.ExpressionWrapper) to specify the **`output_field`** so that you can avoid unwanted errors.

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;b&gt;from django.db import models&lt;/b&gt;

# for annotation
annotated_queryset = Foo.objects.annotate(
    &lt;b&gt;duration=models.ExpressionWrapper(models.F(&#39;date_end&#39;) - models.F(&#39;date_start&#39;),
                                      output_field=models.DurationField())&lt;/b&gt;)

# for filtering
&lt;b&gt;from datetime import timedelta&lt;/b&gt;

